Uses of Package
xyz.morphia

  • Packages that use xyz.morphia 
    Package Description
    xyz.morphia
    This is the base package for all Morphia classes.
    xyz.morphia.aggregation
    Defines various elements for the creation and processing of aggregation pipelines.
    xyz.morphia.dao
    Defines basic DAO types
    xyz.morphia.mapping
    Provides types used for mapping
    xyz.morphia.mapping.cache
    Provides various caching entities
    xyz.morphia.mapping.lazy
    Provides support for lazy references
    xyz.morphia.mapping.lazy.proxy
    Provides support for proxies
    xyz.morphia.mapping.validation
    Provides validation mechanisms to check mapping metadata
    xyz.morphia.mapping.validation.fieldrules
    Defines field level validations
    xyz.morphia.query
    Defines the query capabilities for Morphia
  • Classes in xyz.morphia used by xyz.morphia 
    Class and Description
    AdvancedDatastore
    This interface exposes advanced Datastore features, like interacting with DBObject and low-level options.
    Datastore
    Datastore interface to get/delete/save objects
    DatastoreImpl
    Deprecated. 
    This is an internal implementation of a published API. No public alternative planned.
    DeleteOptions
    The options to apply when removing documents from the DBCollection
    EntityInterceptor
    Interface for intercepting @Entity lifecycle events
    FindAndModifyOptions
    The options for find and modify operations.
    InsertOptions
    Options related to insertion of documents into MongoDB.
    Key
    The key object; this class is take from the app-engine datastore (mostly) implementation.
    MapReduceOptions
    This defines options that can be applied to a mapreduce job
    MapreduceResults
    Stores the results of a map reduce operation
    MapreduceResults.Stats
    This class represents various statistics about a map reduce operation
    MapreduceType
    Deprecated. 
    use MapReduceCommand.OutputType instead
    Morphia 
    UpdateOptions
    The options to apply when updating documents in the DBCollection
    ValidationBuilder
    This is an internal class subject to change and removal.
